A towering structure of horizontal translucent layers floating in space, each layer glowing with different jewel-toned colors (emerald, sapphire, amber, ruby) and connected by delicate vertical light streams passing through them. The layers are made of crystalline glass-like material with intricate circuit patterns visible within. Below the layered structure, scattered broken vertical columns (representing old silos) crumble into geometric fragments. The scene is rendered in a Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, dreamy atmospheric lighting, wispy clouds in a gradient sunset sky of peach and lavender, and tiny floating particles of light drifting between the layers. The composition emphasizes the elegant horizontal harmony of the floating platform contrasted against the rigid broken verticals below.
